WEBVTT Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.805
Immersive teaching shows how technology can support the

00:00:02.805 --> 00:00:04.005
full learning

00:00:04.005 --> 00:00:04.605
cycle.

00:00:04.605 --> 00:00:07.311
Before class, teachers work with intelligent tools to

00:00:07.311 --> 00:00:10.265
generate a personalized set of practice questions, concise

00:00:10.265 --> 00:00:12.774
content summaries, and key terms tailored to each

00:00:12.774 --> 00:00:13.574
learner.

00:00:13.574 --> 00:00:16.541
The goal is to reduce prep time and quickly identify where

00:00:16.541 --> 00:00:17.341
students

00:00:17.341 --> 00:00:17.941
stand.

00:00:17.941 --> 00:00:20.895
In the classroom, real‑time interactive Q&A keeps students

00:00:20.895 --> 00:00:23.799
engaged, invites immediate discussion, and tests ideas on

00:00:23.799 --> 00:00:25.057
the spot to deepen

00:00:25.057 --> 00:00:26.285
understanding.

00:00:26.285 --> 00:00:29.318
After class, automatic grading handles routine assignments,

00:00:29.318 --> 00:00:32.223
delivering instant feedback and freeing teachers to focus

00:00:32.223 --> 00:00:33.675
on guidance and higher‑value

00:00:33.675 --> 00:00:34.175
work.

00:00:34.175 --> 00:00:37.036
Three pillars—tailored practice, active participation,

00:00:37.036 --> 00:00:39.669
timely feedback—link preparation, instruction, and

00:00:39.669 --> 00:00:40.769
assessment.

00:00:40.769 --> 00:00:43.674
Before class, teachers collaborate with intelligent tools

00:00:43.674 --> 00:00:46.094
to build a personalized practice set for each

00:00:46.094 --> 00:00:46.894
learner.

00:00:46.894 --> 00:00:49.852
The system analyzes prior results, then generates targeted

00:00:49.852 --> 00:00:52.359
questions, quick content summaries, and essential

00:00:52.359 --> 00:00:53.259
keywords.

00:00:53.259 --> 00:00:56.323
This tailored preparation reduces planning time and gives a

00:00:56.323 --> 00:00:58.928
clear view of each student’s current understanding,

00:00:58.928 --> 00:01:00.142
strengths, and

00:01:00.142 --> 00:01:00.642
gaps.

00:01:00.642 --> 00:01:03.438
In turn, teachers enter class with a precise map of

00:01:03.438 --> 00:01:06.314
learning needs, ready to guide students through targeted

00:01:06.314 --> 00:01:07.414
activities.

00:01:07.414 --> 00:01:10.395
With this foundation, instruction can adapt in real time,

00:01:10.395 --> 00:01:12.999
keeping pace with diverse learners and accelerating

00:01:12.999 --> 00:01:14.099
progress for

00:01:14.099 --> 00:01:14.999
everyone.
